1
00:00:01,084 --> 00:00:05,380
[Azuelo] <i>We received intel earlier</i>
<i>regarding Agent Reyes's whereabouts.</i>

2
00:00:05,463 --> 00:00:06,881
How can we verify if that's accurate?

3
00:00:06,965 --> 00:00:08,133
Who did it come from, sir?

4
00:00:08,216 --> 00:00:09,676
I'm ready to risk it.

5
00:00:09,759 --> 00:00:11,010
Who's coming with me?

6
00:00:11,094 --> 00:00:12,095
Where's Sir Felix?

7
00:00:12,178 --> 00:00:15,265
We have reason to believe that Domingo

8
00:00:15,348 --> 00:00:16,850
is working with the syndicate.

9
00:00:16,933 --> 00:00:19,310
[Felix] <i>They're starting to suspect me.</i>

10
00:00:19,811 --> 00:00:23,314
<i>I need to take out my enemies</i>
<i>here one at a time.</i>

11
00:00:23,398 --> 00:00:25,734
Seems like Reyes isn't going
to open his mouth at all.

12
00:00:25,817 --> 00:00:27,694
I don't want him to die yet,

13
00:00:27,777 --> 00:00:30,030
<i>because if he does,</i>
<i>we won't be able to find out</i>

14
00:00:30,113 --> 00:00:31,614
what Ahmad told him.

15
00:00:31,698 --> 00:00:33,033
What should we do about Reyes?

16
00:00:33,116 --> 00:00:34,242
Kill him.

17
00:00:34,325 --> 00:00:35,160
[gun cocks]

18
00:00:37,412 --> 00:00:38,621
[agent, in English] <i>We're in position.</i>

19
00:00:39,581 --> 00:00:40,665
[rapid gunfire]

20
00:00:40,749 --> 00:00:41,541
What happened?

21
00:00:41,624 --> 00:00:43,334
[man] <i>Sir, we're being ambushed</i>
<i>by the TFA!</i>

22
00:00:44,627 --> 00:00:46,212
I won't let you catch me alive!

23
00:00:46,296 --> 00:00:47,255
[gunshots]

24
00:00:49,424 --> 00:00:52,010
[young Gabriel] <i>Marcus, you're saved!</i>

25
00:00:52,093 --> 00:00:53,094
- [Espina] <i>Marcus!</i>
- Bro…

26
00:00:53,678 --> 00:00:55,138
[Espina] <i>Bro, you're safe now.</i>

27
00:00:55,638 --> 00:00:56,973
I got you.

28
00:00:58,475 --> 00:00:59,851
- [groans]
- [Espina] Bro!

29
00:00:59,934 --> 00:01:02,020
Bro, we're almost there. Bro, let's go!

30
00:01:02,103 --> 00:01:05,023
[tense music playing]

31
00:01:06,649 --> 00:01:08,485
- [thunder roaring]
- [cries]

32
00:01:08,568 --> 00:01:10,403
[Manuel] <i>Marcus escaped?!</i>

33
00:01:10,487 --> 00:01:11,738
They captured General Ocampo too.

34
00:01:11,821 --> 00:01:12,697
[screaming]

35
00:01:13,823 --> 00:01:17,577
Major General Leopoldo Ocampo!

36
00:01:17,660 --> 00:01:20,914
You're among those who ruin
this institution!

37
00:01:23,708 --> 00:01:26,002
[Jalil] <i>I'm the doctor's missing son.</i>

38
00:01:26,085 --> 00:01:28,004
<i>Marcus and I are brothers.</i>

39
00:01:28,087 --> 00:01:29,923
I'm Gabriel.

40
00:01:30,632 --> 00:01:32,008
[Jamilah] <i>Father has made his decision.</i>

41
00:01:32,091 --> 00:01:33,927
[Datu Rahman] <i>I'm scared to face Jalil.</i>

42
00:01:34,010 --> 00:01:37,096
I'm sure he'll understand why you did it.

43
00:01:37,847 --> 00:01:41,142
[Felix] <i>Will you finally take me</i>
<i>to Jalil Abubakar?</i>

44
00:01:42,727 --> 00:01:47,899
[mysterious theme music playing]

45
00:02:12,006 --> 00:02:12,966
[grunts]

46
00:02:15,135 --> 00:02:16,970
[in Tausug] Thank you, Uncle Omar.

47
00:02:17,053 --> 00:02:20,140
- [in Tausug] Thank you, Omar.
- Sure. I'll see you later.

48
00:02:20,223 --> 00:02:21,057
[in Arabic] God willing.

49
00:02:21,141 --> 00:02:22,976
- [in Arabic] God willing.
- [in Arabic] God willing.

50
00:02:28,773 --> 00:02:32,986
[suspenseful music playing]

51
00:02:48,126 --> 00:02:49,502
Jamilah. Father.

52
00:02:49,586 --> 00:02:50,962
Jalil, my son.

53
00:02:53,214 --> 00:02:55,967
[sighs] Jamilah… Father…

54
00:02:56,050 --> 00:02:59,679
[morose music playing]

55
00:02:59,762 --> 00:03:01,639
My memories are slowly coming back.

56
00:03:05,685 --> 00:03:07,228
I already know the truth.

57
00:03:10,231 --> 00:03:11,608
Doctor Teresa…

58
00:03:13,067 --> 00:03:14,444
and Marcus…

59
00:03:14,944 --> 00:03:16,654
They are my missing family.

60
00:03:21,576 --> 00:03:23,912
- [sighs]
- [Jamilah] Jalil.

61
00:03:26,956 --> 00:03:29,459
That's what Father wanted
to tell you earlier.

62
00:03:29,959 --> 00:03:32,378
That's why he wants
to talk to you in person.

63
00:03:40,386 --> 00:03:41,346
[inhales sharply]

64
00:03:43,056 --> 00:03:44,057
Son.

65
00:03:47,894 --> 00:03:50,813
I am not the innocent person
you think I am.

66
00:03:50,897 --> 00:03:51,773
[inhales sharply]

67
00:03:53,942 --> 00:03:55,818
I was part of…

68
00:03:55,902 --> 00:04:00,031
the syndicate formed
by Colonel Napoleon Marcelino.

69
00:04:01,199 --> 00:04:04,118
We smuggled illegal firearms.

70
00:04:04,744 --> 00:04:06,246
We stirred up chaos.

71
00:04:07,497 --> 00:04:09,290
- Father…
- [Datu Rahman inhales sharply]

72
00:04:09,374 --> 00:04:12,293
But we weren't in it just for the money.

73
00:04:13,294 --> 00:04:16,673
We did it to weaken the government.

74
00:04:19,926 --> 00:04:22,929
As well as to easily gain power.

75
00:04:27,934 --> 00:04:30,520
That's when-- That's when
I met your father.

76
00:04:32,939 --> 00:04:33,940
Victor.

77
00:04:34,983 --> 00:04:36,359
[inhales sharply]

78
00:04:36,442 --> 00:04:38,736
After some time, Victor and I had a talk.

79
00:04:39,445 --> 00:04:42,365
We saw that a lot of people
were getting dragged into the mess

80
00:04:42,448 --> 00:04:46,828
of what we were doing,
innocent people dying.

81
00:04:47,412 --> 00:04:49,747
So we decided to leave the syndicate.

82
00:04:51,457 --> 00:04:53,042
The incident on…

83
00:04:54,585 --> 00:04:56,254
the M/V Doña Emilia…

84
00:04:59,799 --> 00:05:01,926
We tried to stop it from happening.

85
00:05:04,095 --> 00:05:07,724
We tried to stop the explosion,
but we couldn't do anything.

86
00:05:07,807 --> 00:05:08,975
We failed.

87
00:05:10,143 --> 00:05:11,269
And unfortunately,

88
00:05:12,437 --> 00:05:13,688
that's when Victor…

89
00:05:14,981 --> 00:05:17,817
your father, died.

90
00:05:19,902 --> 00:05:21,571
But before he passed away,

91
00:05:22,488 --> 00:05:25,700
he asked me to save you and your brother.

92
00:05:26,367 --> 00:05:27,368
As well as your mother.

93
00:05:30,038 --> 00:05:33,291
Believe me, Jalil. I looked
for you everywhere.

94
00:05:33,374 --> 00:05:35,001
[somber music playing]

95
00:05:35,585 --> 00:05:38,546
But I couldn't find them.
I could only find you,

96
00:05:38,629 --> 00:05:40,798
so I was only able to save you.

97
00:05:43,551 --> 00:05:44,427
[Jalil sniffling]

98
00:05:44,510 --> 00:05:45,720
[sighs]

99
00:05:46,679 --> 00:05:48,806
Though Victor and I were always together,

100
00:05:48,890 --> 00:05:53,186
not once did we ever talk
about our own families,

101
00:05:53,269 --> 00:05:56,314
our-- our personal lives.

102
00:05:56,397 --> 00:05:59,442
Because the syndicate
could use it against us.

103
00:06:01,152 --> 00:06:03,529
That's why I couldn't return you

104
00:06:03,613 --> 00:06:04,989
to your mother,

105
00:06:05,073 --> 00:06:07,658
because I didn't know
where they were going.

106
00:06:07,742 --> 00:06:09,660
I didn't know where they lived.

107
00:06:11,329 --> 00:06:13,122
I also thought that…

108
00:06:14,248 --> 00:06:17,168
they might've sunk with the ship too.

109
00:06:17,251 --> 00:06:19,754
[morose music playing]

110
00:06:20,338 --> 00:06:24,342
I also had to hide
from the syndicate, Jalil.

111
00:06:25,259 --> 00:06:27,887
So I changed my name.

112
00:06:29,013 --> 00:06:30,681
From Hassan Wadi… [inhales]

113
00:06:31,641 --> 00:06:33,267
I changed it to…

114
00:06:33,351 --> 00:06:35,103
Rahman Abubakar.

115
00:06:39,190 --> 00:06:44,862
I was scared that if
they found out where I was,

116
00:06:44,946 --> 00:06:47,949
they would kill me, and you could

117
00:06:48,658 --> 00:06:49,826
get involved too.

118
00:06:50,993 --> 00:06:52,829
And I didn't want that to happen.

119
00:06:54,705 --> 00:06:56,082
I didn't want you to get dragged…

120
00:06:58,376 --> 00:07:00,711
into the mess caused by my actions.

121
00:07:04,215 --> 00:07:07,593
- Jalil…
- [breathing shakily]

122
00:07:08,177 --> 00:07:09,178
[inhales sharply]

123
00:07:09,262 --> 00:07:13,599
This is why Father wanted
to talk to you in person.

124
00:07:14,350 --> 00:07:15,852
[Jamilah cries]

125
00:07:15,935 --> 00:07:20,773
But he was worried
that you would get mad at him.

126
00:07:25,611 --> 00:07:26,446
‪[dramatic whoosh]

127
00:07:32,827 --> 00:07:34,954
- [Jamilah crying]
- Please forgive me, son.

128
00:07:36,622 --> 00:07:38,249
[Datu Rahman] I'm sorry, Jalil.

129
00:07:38,332 --> 00:07:39,375
[Jamilah sobbing]

130
00:07:41,043 --> 00:07:42,879
Please forgive me.

131
00:07:44,255 --> 00:07:45,590
I'm sorry.

132
00:07:45,673 --> 00:07:50,803
- [sobs]
- [Jalil sniffles]

133
00:07:54,056 --> 00:07:55,099
Father…

134
00:07:57,560 --> 00:08:00,062
What are you apologizing for?

135
00:08:02,648 --> 00:08:04,192
If it weren't for you…

136
00:08:04,275 --> 00:08:08,070
[mellow music playing]

137
00:08:08,154 --> 00:08:11,282
If you hadn't risked your life to save me…

138
00:08:11,365 --> 00:08:12,325
[inhales sharply]

139
00:08:13,075 --> 00:08:14,869
…I would be dead by now.

140
00:08:18,664 --> 00:08:21,209
You and Jamilah made me feel…

141
00:08:22,376 --> 00:08:23,544
[Jamilah sniffles]

142
00:08:24,337 --> 00:08:26,964
…what it's like to be loved by a family.

143
00:08:29,842 --> 00:08:32,428
Father, I am who I am today
because of you.

144
00:08:35,056 --> 00:08:36,307
[sniffles]

145
00:08:36,390 --> 00:08:37,642
[Jalil] And because of you…

146
00:08:38,976 --> 00:08:41,062
I could be with my family again.

147
00:08:43,064 --> 00:08:44,690
[breathes shakily]

148
00:08:44,774 --> 00:08:47,068
When all of this is over…

149
00:08:47,735 --> 00:08:51,489
I will have the opportunity
to know them more.

150
00:08:52,657 --> 00:08:55,159
Father, I'm not angry with you.

151
00:08:56,244 --> 00:08:58,996
I understand why you had
to keep this from me.

152
00:08:59,497 --> 00:09:00,706
[Jamilah sniffles]

153
00:09:00,790 --> 00:09:03,292
And I know you're correcting
what you've done.

154
00:09:04,669 --> 00:09:06,337
Your mistakes.

155
00:09:06,420 --> 00:09:08,089
[softly] I'm sorry, Jalil.

156
00:09:08,172 --> 00:09:10,508
That's why I will finish my mission…

157
00:09:10,591 --> 00:09:14,011
to put an end to all of this chaos.

158
00:09:15,263 --> 00:09:16,764
[Jalil sniffles]

159
00:09:17,765 --> 00:09:20,184
I will punish those who need
to get punished.

160
00:09:21,018 --> 00:09:23,312
So you will be set free from your past.

161
00:09:23,938 --> 00:09:25,898
Thank you so much, Jalil.

162
00:09:26,566 --> 00:09:29,735
- [gentle music playing]
- [sobbing]

163
00:09:29,819 --> 00:09:33,739
[Datu Rahman] <i>Thank you so much, son.</i>

164
00:09:34,532 --> 00:09:37,076
[Jalil] <i>Thank you so much, Father.</i>

165
00:09:38,327 --> 00:09:39,954
[Jalil] Thank you, Jamilah.

166
00:09:42,999 --> 00:09:45,334
I love you.

167
00:09:45,418 --> 00:09:49,380
[Datu Rahman] <i>I love you so much too, son.</i>

168
00:09:49,463 --> 00:09:51,382
<i>Please forgive me.</i>

169
00:09:59,640 --> 00:10:02,351
<i>Thank you so much to you too, Jamilah.</i>

170
00:10:03,686 --> 00:10:05,521
<i>I love you so much.</i>

171
00:10:05,605 --> 00:10:06,480
[sobs]

172
00:10:06,564 --> 00:10:07,607
[Jamilah] <i>I love you too.</i>

173
00:10:07,690 --> 00:10:10,318
[sniffles]

174
00:10:24,749 --> 00:10:29,462
[music turns suspenseful]

175
00:10:38,137 --> 00:10:40,431
What is Espina doing here?

176
00:10:46,979 --> 00:10:49,523
[Jalil] Take care of them, okay?

177
00:11:02,036 --> 00:11:05,289
<i>Jalil Abubakar, a member of CDSU.</i>

178
00:11:05,873 --> 00:11:09,543
<i>From what I know, he trains new recruits</i>

179
00:11:09,627 --> 00:11:11,671
<i>across Mindanao.</i>

180
00:11:15,132 --> 00:11:17,301
[Ethan] "Jalil Abubakar."

181
00:11:19,470 --> 00:11:24,642
Sir, the CDSU really has
no records of a Jalil Abubakar.

182
00:11:26,310 --> 00:11:27,436
Sir.

183
00:11:27,520 --> 00:11:31,482
<i>The cop with glasses took in</i>
<i>Datu Rahman right there earlier.</i>

184
00:11:34,902 --> 00:11:37,196
Major Allan Espina…

185
00:11:39,156 --> 00:11:40,825
and Jalil Abubakar…

186
00:11:43,661 --> 00:11:44,995
are the same person.

187
00:11:50,960 --> 00:11:51,961
[groans]

188
00:11:53,879 --> 00:11:56,048
[knocking on door]

189
00:11:57,174 --> 00:12:00,636
I had just taken a break for ten minutes
and there are already patients?

190
00:12:01,345 --> 00:12:02,388
[sighs]

191
00:12:09,228 --> 00:12:10,479
Allan?

192
00:12:12,481 --> 00:12:13,315
Um.

193
00:12:14,483 --> 00:12:15,568
Come in.

194
00:12:16,277 --> 00:12:20,865
[morose music playing]

195
00:12:28,539 --> 00:12:29,874
Allan, what's wrong?

196
00:12:34,086 --> 00:12:35,963
Is something bothering you, son?

197
00:13:01,864 --> 00:13:06,994
[morose music intensifies]

198
00:13:08,329 --> 00:13:11,123
[Espina] In my dream, I had a brother.

199
00:13:11,790 --> 00:13:15,085
He was… trying to save me.

200
00:13:17,338 --> 00:13:19,507
[Teresa] What if my son is still alive?

201
00:13:20,216 --> 00:13:21,926
I wonder how he's doing?

202
00:13:22,843 --> 00:13:24,011
[soft chuckle]

203
00:13:24,512 --> 00:13:26,555
I want to hug him so badly.

204
00:13:28,140 --> 00:13:32,019
Son, if something's bothering you,
you can always come to me.

205
00:13:33,062 --> 00:13:34,813
- I'll listen to you.
- [sobs]

206
00:13:36,315 --> 00:13:38,317
I'll be here for you

207
00:13:38,400 --> 00:13:40,236
until you feel better again.

208
00:13:40,319 --> 00:13:41,278
[Espina] Mm.

209
00:13:41,362 --> 00:13:46,534
[Espina groans]

210
00:13:47,368 --> 00:13:48,452
Thank you.

211
00:13:50,579 --> 00:13:52,164
Thank you, Doctor Teresa.

212
00:14:02,132 --> 00:14:04,343
[music fades]

213
00:14:04,426 --> 00:14:06,345
Sir Marcus, how are you feeling?

214
00:14:06,428 --> 00:14:08,305
I'm okay. I'm still recovering.

215
00:14:09,890 --> 00:14:11,058
[Marcus] Everything still hurts,

216
00:14:11,141 --> 00:14:13,644
but thankfully, the painkillers
are helping. [soft chuckle]

217
00:14:15,062 --> 00:14:16,021
[agent] Any news?

218
00:14:16,105 --> 00:14:18,566
Has General Ocampo talked, sir?

219
00:14:19,942 --> 00:14:24,154
[morose music playing]

220
00:14:26,907 --> 00:14:30,411
[Jamilah] Jalil, now that
you know the truth,

221
00:14:31,120 --> 00:14:34,164
are you going to tell Sir Marcus
and Doctor Teresa

222
00:14:34,999 --> 00:14:36,208
that you're Gabriel?

223
00:14:38,752 --> 00:14:39,753
Not yet.

224
00:14:41,255 --> 00:14:43,173
I need to finish my mission first.

225
00:14:44,717 --> 00:14:45,885
Once everything's over,

226
00:14:47,052 --> 00:14:49,138
I'll tell them they're my mother and…

227
00:14:50,389 --> 00:14:51,557
my brother.

228
00:14:55,311 --> 00:14:56,687
- [agent] Okay, sir.
- [Marcus] Alright.

229
00:15:05,863 --> 00:15:06,739
Bro.

230
00:15:08,115 --> 00:15:09,617
You're finally here.

231
00:15:10,534 --> 00:15:11,577
We need to talk.

232
00:15:17,124 --> 00:15:18,125
Bro.

233
00:15:19,001 --> 00:15:20,169
Are you okay?

234
00:15:22,588 --> 00:15:23,756
I'm okay…

235
00:15:24,965 --> 00:15:26,133
brother.

236
00:15:27,760 --> 00:15:29,219
What do we need to talk about?

237
00:15:31,722 --> 00:15:32,973
Let's go to the war room.

238
00:15:46,487 --> 00:15:47,696
[music fades]

239
00:15:47,780 --> 00:15:51,533
[stirring music playing]

240
00:15:51,617 --> 00:15:53,160
I managed to take some photos and videos

241
00:15:53,243 --> 00:15:56,205
we could've used as evidence.

242
00:15:56,830 --> 00:15:58,123
[Espina] Where are they?

243
00:15:58,207 --> 00:16:00,042
They smashed my phone.

244
00:16:01,502 --> 00:16:02,878
[grunts]

245
00:16:07,174 --> 00:16:08,342
It's okay.

246
00:16:09,218 --> 00:16:11,428
We'll find more evidence.

247
00:16:13,013 --> 00:16:14,723
[phone chimes]

248
00:16:20,229 --> 00:16:22,523
Sir, you need to see this.

249
00:16:26,944 --> 00:16:29,947
[music intensifies]

250
00:16:31,573 --> 00:16:35,202
Someone like Ahmad Mustapha

251
00:16:35,285 --> 00:16:39,456
is impossible to match
and even harder to replace.

252
00:16:39,957 --> 00:16:43,127
[music becomes foreboding]

253
00:16:43,210 --> 00:16:47,840
We've fought side by side
as brothers for many years.

254
00:16:47,923 --> 00:16:51,343
[in English] <i>That's why this is not</i>
<i>an easy decision to make.</i>

255
00:16:52,136 --> 00:16:54,471
<i>I've thought about it for a long time.</i>

256
00:16:54,555 --> 00:16:56,598
There are only a handful of people

257
00:16:57,182 --> 00:16:59,560
I trust completely.

258
00:17:01,770 --> 00:17:03,689
That's why I've decided

259
00:17:04,773 --> 00:17:07,151
that my new Chief of Staff…

260
00:17:07,234 --> 00:17:10,946
[music intensifies]

261
00:17:11,030 --> 00:17:14,199
…will be General Manuel Carillo.

262
00:17:15,659 --> 00:17:20,372
[dramatic sting]

263
00:17:25,127 --> 00:17:26,670
Madam President,

264
00:17:27,588 --> 00:17:30,883
it's a great honor

265
00:17:30,966 --> 00:17:35,179
to be given the opportunity

266
00:17:35,262 --> 00:17:39,892
to serve the Republic.

267
00:17:42,019 --> 00:17:46,982
There are plans underway

268
00:17:48,067 --> 00:17:50,319
to destabilize the government.

269
00:17:50,402 --> 00:17:55,074
[foreboding music playing]

270
00:17:55,157 --> 00:17:56,241
This…

271
00:17:57,117 --> 00:18:00,079
This is exactly what he's planning!

272
00:18:00,162 --> 00:18:05,417
He must've orchestrated
the assassination plot

273
00:18:05,501 --> 00:18:07,795
to gain the President's trust!

274
00:18:07,878 --> 00:18:10,422
And now, he is more powerful.

275
00:18:10,506 --> 00:18:12,132
He tricked us.

276
00:18:12,216 --> 00:18:14,927
We thought we had the upper hand,
but we didn't.

277
00:18:15,010 --> 00:18:18,597
[tense music playing]

278
00:18:18,680 --> 00:18:24,394
Ahmad was trying
to prevent the destabilization

279
00:18:24,478 --> 00:18:29,233
until the last moment of his life.

280
00:18:29,316 --> 00:18:33,445
[grim music playing]

281
00:18:33,529 --> 00:18:37,491
And that was also the reason

282
00:18:38,534 --> 00:18:40,994
my dear friend was killed.

283
00:18:43,247 --> 00:18:49,128
Just recently, I almost fell victim

284
00:18:49,211 --> 00:18:53,340
to these people

285
00:18:53,924 --> 00:18:58,011
when they attempted to assassinate me.

286
00:18:59,763 --> 00:19:02,391
Oh my goodness. What's going on?

287
00:19:04,852 --> 00:19:10,315
[Manuel] <i>Because I've been</i>
<i>investigating this case</i>

288
00:19:10,399 --> 00:19:12,109
for a long time.

289
00:19:13,235 --> 00:19:14,611
[in English] Goddammit!

290
00:19:14,695 --> 00:19:19,491
[tense music playing]

291
00:19:25,080 --> 00:19:29,585
And according to my investigation,

292
00:19:30,836 --> 00:19:35,257
<i>the people plotting this destabilization</i>

293
00:19:35,340 --> 00:19:39,720
<i>are the same people</i>
<i>distributing illegal weapons</i>

294
00:19:39,803 --> 00:19:41,430
<i>across the country.</i>

295
00:19:42,639 --> 00:19:49,229
Because they want chaos

296
00:19:49,313 --> 00:19:52,274
and violence to spread

297
00:19:52,357 --> 00:19:55,861
<i>so the people will lose</i>

298
00:19:55,944 --> 00:20:01,867
confidence and trust in the government.

299
00:20:04,077 --> 00:20:07,372
And the leader

300
00:20:09,291 --> 00:20:10,709
of this group…

301
00:20:15,214 --> 00:20:18,425
is the man in this photo.

302
00:20:23,222 --> 00:20:25,724
Hassan Wadi.

303
00:20:33,440 --> 00:20:34,566
Gabriel?!

304
00:20:37,736 --> 00:20:39,363
[loud explosion]

305
00:20:42,866 --> 00:20:47,621
[suspenseful music playing]

306
00:20:48,413 --> 00:20:52,376
He has been the leader of this group

307
00:20:52,459 --> 00:20:54,169
for nearly 30 years.

308
00:20:55,379 --> 00:20:59,299
And for the longest time,

309
00:20:59,383 --> 00:21:03,679
we couldn't find him.

310
00:21:05,055 --> 00:21:06,390
[in Arabic] Oh, Allah…

311
00:21:06,473 --> 00:21:07,849
[breath quivers]

312
00:21:09,017 --> 00:21:12,229
[Manuel] Because all along

313
00:21:12,312 --> 00:21:16,316
this Hassan Wadi, this criminal,

314
00:21:16,984 --> 00:21:20,279
this master manipulator,

315
00:21:21,071 --> 00:21:25,367
has been hiding in plain sight

316
00:21:26,159 --> 00:21:31,498
under the alias Datu Rahman Abubakar.

317
00:21:34,459 --> 00:21:39,589
- [tense music playing]
- [dramatic stinging]

318
00:21:54,813 --> 00:21:59,276
[dramatic sting]

319
00:22:00,902 --> 00:22:07,659
<i>And he has been conspiring</i>
<i>with none other than</i>

320
00:22:07,743 --> 00:22:10,537
<i>his own son.</i>

321
00:22:12,456 --> 00:22:15,250
Jalil Abubakar.

322
00:22:16,752 --> 00:22:21,465
- [tense music intensifies]
- [rapid dramatic stinging]

323
00:22:31,767 --> 00:22:32,601
‪[dramatic sting]

324
00:22:36,730 --> 00:22:37,564
‪[dramatic sting]

325
00:22:39,024 --> 00:22:39,858
‪[dramatic sting]

326
00:22:44,237 --> 00:22:48,658
- Hassan, Datu Rahman…
- [camera shutters clicking]

327
00:22:49,159 --> 00:22:51,161
whoever you are,

328
00:22:51,828 --> 00:22:56,291
you betrayed Ahmad Mustapha.

329
00:22:57,501 --> 00:23:01,963
You exploited your shared faith

330
00:23:02,047 --> 00:23:06,051
to gain his trust.

331
00:23:06,134 --> 00:23:07,886
He trusted you.

332
00:23:07,969 --> 00:23:12,808
And what did you do in return?

333
00:23:13,975 --> 00:23:16,019
You killed him!

334
00:23:17,687 --> 00:23:21,274
Because he uncovered your plot

335
00:23:21,358 --> 00:23:25,028
to destabilize the country.

336
00:23:26,321 --> 00:23:32,119
You even blew up
that bus full of tourists.

337
00:23:33,411 --> 00:23:38,083
And you were able
to do these things, Rahman,

338
00:23:38,166 --> 00:23:40,377
because you still have

339
00:23:41,128 --> 00:23:47,717
someone inside the NLEA working for you.

340
00:23:47,801 --> 00:23:50,095
[dramatic sting]

341
00:23:50,178 --> 00:23:54,516
And you can't deny, Rahman Abubakar,

342
00:23:54,599 --> 00:23:56,810
that you have been a menace to society

343
00:23:56,893 --> 00:23:59,271
since the very beginning!

344
00:23:59,855 --> 00:24:03,775
Because you're the one
Ahmad was referring to

345
00:24:03,859 --> 00:24:09,281
who blew up the M/V Doña Emilia.

346
00:24:09,364 --> 00:24:14,703
[dramatic sting]

347
00:24:18,874 --> 00:24:22,711
But you won't be able
to cause any more harm.

348
00:24:24,129 --> 00:24:28,133
[in English] Not on my watch.

349
00:24:28,216 --> 00:24:31,094
[dramatic sting]

350
00:24:31,178 --> 00:24:33,346
[camera shutters clicking]

351
00:24:33,430 --> 00:24:34,222
[in English] Goddammit!

352
00:24:34,306 --> 00:24:35,599
You bastard!

353
00:24:36,641 --> 00:24:39,603
[camera shutters clicking]

354
00:24:39,686 --> 00:24:40,604
Thank you.

355
00:24:46,318 --> 00:24:48,403
- [Ocampo] <i>Bravo!</i>
- [clapping]

356
00:24:50,530 --> 00:24:52,115
[camera shutters clicking]

357
00:24:52,199 --> 00:24:57,037
[dramatic sting]

358
00:25:14,387 --> 00:25:16,681
You've been missing for 30 years.

359
00:25:16,765 --> 00:25:19,184
[Jamilah] <i>Why don't you</i>
<i>tell them the truth?</i>

360
00:25:19,267 --> 00:25:21,728
[Jalil] <i>I've been implicated</i>
<i>as Father's accomplice.</i>

361
00:25:21,811 --> 00:25:23,396
<i>They can't be associated with me.</i>

362
00:25:23,480 --> 00:25:28,360
I'm so close to getting revenge
on Jalil Abubakar.

363
00:25:30,528 --> 00:25:34,324
[Marcus] <i>Datu Rahman was the man</i>
<i>who blew up the M/V Doña Emilia.</i>

364
00:25:34,407 --> 00:25:35,450
<i>I will uncover the truth.</i>

365
00:25:35,533 --> 00:25:38,328
[Omar] Not everything
General Carillo said was true.

366
00:25:38,411 --> 00:25:40,121
I hope you can forgive me.

367
00:25:40,205 --> 00:25:42,958
[Marcus] Are you responsible
for my brother's death?!

368
00:25:43,041 --> 00:25:47,003
[Manuel] <i>People must be furious</i>
<i>with Datu Rahman.</i>

369
00:25:47,087 --> 00:25:49,965
We're inching closer to the New Republic!

370
00:25:50,048 --> 00:25:51,549
- Yes!
- Yes!

371
00:25:51,633 --> 00:25:52,968
[Jamilah] <i>Jalil?</i>

372
00:25:53,051 --> 00:25:54,469
[Jamilah] <i>Father!</i>
